# STM32 VSCode Demo

My first STM32 project using VS Code + STM32 Extension + CMake workflow.

## Board
- STM32F407G-DISC1
- STM32F407VG MCU

## Development Environment
- VS Code
- STM32CubeMX
- STM32 Extension for VS Code
- ARM GCC Toolchain
- CMake + Ninja
- ST-LINK

## Features
- PD12 ~ PD15 onboard LED blinking
- HAL GPIO control
- HAL delay timing

## Code Example

```c
HAL_GPIO_TogglePin(GPIOD, LED_BLUE_Pin);

HAL_GPIO_TogglePin(GPIOD, LED_GREEN_Pin);

HAL_GPIO_TogglePin(GPIOD, LED_ORANGE_Pin);

HAL_GPIO_TogglePin(GPIOD, LED_RED_Pin);

HAL_Delay(300);
```
## Learning Goal

This project is used to practice:

- STM32 HAL development
- GPIO control
- VS Code STM32 workflow
- Git & GitHub integration
- Embedded firmware debugging

## Debug
- ST-LINK debugging enabled
- Breakpoint and register watch tested successfully

